ing outgoing rules were replaced by the default rules. (Bug 180; agmtek)</li><li>ISDN4K-utils is compiled better now.</li><li>Install c_icap files that were missing from Update7.</li><li>Remove old libs and files that were left behind during previous updates. We need to delete old files/program/libraries that may have security bugs in them.</li><li>Change more scripts to use modern URL-fetching perl libs. (Bug 184; panda)</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0;"><b><u>User interface</u></b></p><ul style="margin:0 0 0 0;"><li>Manually setting the time works again. (Bitbeisser)</li><li>Adjust time zone array key versus time zone display text. This fixes problems with using time zones that have spaces in the names.</li><li>The Time UI now describes when the daemon runs and when it serves time to clients. This should help reduce admin confusion.</li><li>We made various twerks and adjustments to the Smoothinfo UI and script (panda)</li><li>We made Various twerks and improvements throughout the UI (panda)</li><li>The UI help for all of the log pages works again (Etherlord)</li><li>Bandwidthbars: only display IPs that are present on the LAN; the list of IPs can be greatly shortened. (w.hill, panda)</li><li>p3scan/clamav: improve error messages, give hints where to look when it they fail to start.</li><li>We added a way to archive simple settings to a file sent to the browser, and allow the admin to upload an archive to be restored. This replaces the 'backup to floppy' and 'restore from floppy' feature.</li><li>Delete the Alcatel-Thompson USB DSL modem from the UI. It used programs from the speedtouch package which no longer compiled and hadn't been maintained since 2004. (bug 139; panda)</li><li>Display the last page of a multi-page log display (bug 85; panda)</li><li>Add refresh patterns to squid's file (cache) (bug 7; Dataking)</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0;"><b><u>Resolved bugs</u></b></p>Bugs 7, 85, 105, 139, 140, 155, 157, 159, 175, and 177-184 have been resolved.S