009|4a67f85469a973572ff9a67863cc5b38|update9-x86_64|<p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">We improved the UI, resolved a number of bugs, updated a number of packages, and re-released all of the Update8 packages.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">The changes include improving UI usability and error detection and correction, progress toward allowing RED to be a wireless NIC, switch to Libreswan for IPsec, 'locking' kernel headers to v3.4.104, some Meltdown/Spectre mitigations, and elimination of several TLS security issues.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">One user reported a problem with PPPoE not validating/connecting; this has not been resolved either way as yet. See <a style="color:#808080; text-decoration:underline;"  href="https://community.smoothwall.org/forum/viewtopic.php?p=351287#p351287"><i>the initial post</i></a>.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">The nouveau driver for nVidia video cards does not seem to build correctly. If booting hangs and your system uses an nVidia card, you will likely need to remove the nouveau driver (thus letting the system default to the generic VESA driver). See <a style="color:#808080; text-decoration:underline;"  href="https://community.smoothwall.org/bugs/view.php?id=205"><i>bug #205</i></a>.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">Thanks to everyone on the team and in the community who helped identify and root out bugs and problems and helped test.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">See <a style="color:#808080; text-decoration:underline;"  href="https://community.smoothwall.org/forum/viewtopic.php?f=9&t=44029"><i>the forum announcement</i></a> for all of the details.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;">As always, if you experience any problems, support is available via the <a style="color:#808080; text-decoration:underline;"  href="http://community.smoothwall.org/forum/viewforum.php?f=108"><i>Smoothwall Express 3.1 forum</i></a>.</p><p style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;" style="margin:.5em 0 0 0;"><b><u>Updated packages</u></b></p><p style="margin: 0;" st